&gt;&gt; Jenny Bilfield: Thank you.

01:08:11.340 --> 01:08:13.410
Oh, please continue to join us
for just a short amount more

01:08:13.410 --> 01:08:15.880
and then we'll take a
break in a few minutes.

01:08:15.880 --> 01:08:18.160
But one of our many
special guests today,

01:08:18.160 --> 01:08:21.550
it gives me great pleasure to
introduce Barbara Comstock,

01:08:21.550 --> 01:08:23.530
Congresswoman from Virginia.

01:08:23.530 --> 01:08:25.920
Although she recently joined
the Kennedy Center board

01:08:25.920 --> 01:08:28.880
of trustees, Congresswoman
Comstock has been a consistent

01:08:28.880 --> 01:08:31.010
and effective advocate
for the arts,

01:08:31.010 --> 01:08:33.240
having spearhead the
formation of the Arts Caucus

01:08:33.240 --> 01:08:34.830
in the Virginia House
of Delegates

01:08:34.830 --> 01:08:37.020
where she served in that body.

01:08:37.020 --> 01:08:39.060
The congresswoman was
elected this past November

01:08:39.060 --> 01:08:40.780
to her second term in the House,

01:08:40.780 --> 01:08:42.740
representing the
nearby Virginia district

01:08:42.740 --> 01:08:44.040
in the House of Representatives.

01:08:44.040 --> 01:08:45.890
She has been a supporter
for the arts and many

01:08:45.890 --> 01:08:48.280
of our local cultural
organizations.

01:08:48.280 --> 01:08:49.900
We welcome her leadership.

01:08:49.900 --> 01:08:52.090
In the House of Representatives,
the congresswoman serves

01:08:52.090 --> 01:08:54.160
on the Transportation and
Infrastructure Committee,

01:08:54.160 --> 01:08:56.880
as well as the Science, Space
and Technology Committee

01:08:56.880 --> 01:08:58.950
where she is chair of the
subcommittee on research

01:08:58.950 --> 01:09:01.490
and technology, the House
Administration Committee

01:09:01.490 --> 01:09:03.100
in the US House of
Representatives

01:09:03.100 --> 01:09:05.490
and the Bicameral Joint
Economic Committee.

01:09:05.490 --> 01:09:08.120
I now join each of you in
expressing our appreciation

01:09:08.120 --> 01:09:10.420
for the strong voice she has
had in Congress on behalf

01:09:10.420 --> 01:09:13.020
of northern Virginia and
metropolitan Washington.

01:09:13.020 --> 01:09:15.360
We are honored that she is able
to be with us this morning.

01:09:15.360 --> 01:09:19.510
Please join me in welcoming
Congresswoman Barbara Comstock.

01:09:19.510 --> 01:09:28.060
[ Applause ]

01:09:28.060 --> 01:09:30.230
&gt;&gt; BC: Thank you and
good morning to you all.

01:09:30.230 --> 01:09:33.680
It's a pleasure to be here and
to hear that wonderful group.

01:09:33.680 --> 01:09:35.710
How delightful to see them.

01:09:35.710 --> 01:09:38.820
And as I was seeing them walk
out, thinking with this kind

01:09:38.820 --> 01:09:41.980
of mentorship, with this kind of
support, they'll be able to --

01:09:41.980 --> 01:09:43.460
whatever community they go,

01:09:43.460 --> 01:09:47.000
hopefully they will
find a music home

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:49.400
for themselves in
their communities.

01:09:49.400 --> 01:09:52.940
And that's what we're
here celebrating today.

01:09:52.940 --> 01:09:56.390
So I'm honored to be on
the Kennedy Center Board,

01:09:56.390 --> 01:09:59.210
also a member of the Arts
Caucus as was mentioned.

01:09:59.210 --> 01:10:04.080
And also was able to start
an arts caucus in Virginia.

01:10:04.080 --> 01:10:07.710
You know, we know our founding
fathers were patrons of the arts

01:10:07.710 --> 01:10:11.740
and understood what an important
part of our education it is.

01:10:11.740 --> 01:10:14.900
Now it's estimated that there
are over 100,000 musicians

01:10:14.900 --> 01:10:18.310
who perform and approximately
1,600 orchestras throughout

01:10:18.310 --> 01:10:19.610
the country.

01:10:19.610 --> 01:10:21.510
So one of the things
there that I know

01:10:21.510 --> 01:10:25.010
from supporting my own
local orchestra in McClain,

01:10:25.010 --> 01:10:27.450
Virginia where I live,
just over the river,

01:10:27.450 --> 01:10:31.750
is that protecting
our charitable status,

01:10:31.750 --> 01:10:35.190
tax-giving status, helps many
orchestras in our country.

01:10:35.190 --> 01:10:36.790
Because most of them
are organized

01:10:36.790 --> 01:10:39.980
as 501C3 tax exempt
organizations.

01:10:39.980 --> 01:10:45.020
And it's also a great way that
any community, wherever you are,

01:10:45.020 --> 01:10:48.620
can give back and become
part of something local.

01:10:48.620 --> 01:10:51.190
I'm also privileged to
have the Wolf Trap Center

01:10:51.190 --> 01:10:53.570
for the Performing
Arts in my district.

01:10:53.570 --> 01:10:56.540
And one of the things that
we were able to do when I was

01:10:56.540 --> 01:10:59.290
in the state house
was to utilize

01:10:59.290 --> 01:11:03.330
that arts center
for STEAM education.

01:11:03.330 --> 01:11:06.860
So it's not just about STEM and
the science, but also understand

01:11:06.860 --> 01:11:10.750
that arts works together, and
be able to have model programs

01:11:10.750 --> 01:11:14.090
that now they are modeling
throughout the program

01:11:14.090 --> 01:11:16.310
and I believe throughout
the world.

01:11:16.310 --> 01:11:18.530
So young people here, we want

01:11:18.530 --> 01:11:22.400
to catch them even
younger in the arts.

01:11:22.400 --> 01:11:25.680
So we do know we are going
to have some challenges

01:11:25.680 --> 01:11:28.580
on that front coming
up, I imagine.

01:11:28.580 --> 01:11:31.670
But I've always been
supportive of that.

01:11:31.670 --> 01:11:35.030
And last Congress, we
supported equitable access

01:11:35.030 --> 01:11:38.170
to the arts education
in the education bill

01:11:38.170 --> 01:11:43.330
that we reauthorized, where the
bill sets aside approximately 30

01:11:43.330 --> 01:11:45.440
million to high-risk schools

01:11:45.440 --> 01:11:48.110
so they can develop
an arts program.

01:11:48.110 --> 01:11:50.200
Those have been somewhat
in decline and we wanted

01:11:50.200 --> 01:11:54.430
to make sure that we
could reinvigorate that.

01:11:54.430 --> 01:11:59.560
Now we also -- when you
have these local orchestras

01:11:59.560 --> 01:12:03.230
and local arts groups,
local music group,

01:12:03.230 --> 01:12:06.170
you end up really
providing so much support

01:12:06.170 --> 01:12:09.190
for your youth orchestra
too, and mentoring.

01:12:09.190 --> 01:12:11.490
And they see people
who are engaged --

01:12:11.490 --> 01:12:14.760
I know in our local
orchestra we have a conductor

01:12:14.760 --> 01:12:18.270
who not only is the conductor
for the McClain orchestra,

01:12:18.270 --> 01:12:19.990
she travels all around
the country

01:12:19.990 --> 01:12:21.460
and even all around the world.

01:12:21.460 --> 01:12:25.470
So she brings back all of her
experiences and then works

01:12:25.470 --> 01:12:30.710
with her local artists who range
from professional musicians

01:12:30.710 --> 01:12:35.030
who are part of this to doctors
and lawyers and moms at home

01:12:35.030 --> 01:12:40.780
who are sort of getting back
into the field in that way.

01:12:40.780 --> 01:12:45.130
And I am always amazed when
I go to our local concerts

01:12:45.130 --> 01:12:48.840
to see the variety of people
who are in that program,

01:12:48.840 --> 01:12:51.060
and then the quality
of our youth orchestras

01:12:51.060 --> 01:12:53.190
because they are part of this,

01:12:53.190 --> 01:12:55.090
and that's a big part
of their program.

01:12:55.090 --> 01:12:57.440
And they understand the
community support that's going

01:12:57.440 --> 01:12:59.300
to be there for them.

01:12:59.300 --> 01:13:03.070
So I really appreciate the
opportunity to be here.

01:13:03.070 --> 01:13:07.670
It's really something I
think that is a lifelong part

01:13:07.670 --> 01:13:11.640
of the learning process and
that the passion that is brought

01:13:11.640 --> 01:13:15.660
to all of you who are supporters
of the arts, and transmitted

01:13:15.660 --> 01:13:18.360
through all of our
communities and transmitted back

01:13:18.360 --> 01:13:24.370
to our children is a very
important part of the heritage

01:13:24.370 --> 01:13:27.180
that we can pass on as
part of our country.

01:13:27.180 --> 01:13:31.490
That's our privilege to be part
of the Kennedy Center and many

01:13:31.490 --> 01:13:35.610
of my local arts groups in
order to continue that effort.

01:13:35.610 --> 01:13:40.650
So thank you for being here
today, and enjoy your day

01:13:40.650 --> 01:13:45.680
and thank you for your support
and patronage of the arts.

01:13:47.510 --> 01:13:51.040
